Lamiaceae has about 250 genera and 7200 species, occurring in tropical to temperate areas worldwide, except Antarctica. In Brazil, there are approximately 500 native species, with some genera and species introduced and naturalized (
 Harley, 1988, 
 2012; 
 Harley et al., 2004; 
 Harley and Pastore, 2012).
